<lccdd>
<documentation>
  Title: Micro Pattern Gas Detectors Cylindrical Barrel Layer
  Author: @ybedfer
  Status: development
  Version: 3.2
</documentation>

  <define>
    <comment>
      Inner MPGD tracking layer = CyMBaL, in 12 sectors with fish scale layout and realistic segmentation
      Note: MPGDs come in two distinct flavors: pixel and 2DStrip, each tagged
      with a distinctive setting of the "InnerMPGDBarrel_2DStrip" constant.
      - 2DStrip is meant for the Multiple Sensitive Volume implementation of
      the strip digitization in EICrecon's "MPGDTrackerDigi".
      - Two of the Sensitive Volumes, "(phi|Z)StripThinGap", have a meaningful
      Segmentation, with a pitch corresponding to that of the actual detector.
      - The other three Sensitive Volumes are Helpers, used only in the
      processing of MC data. The particulars of their segmentation are
      disregarded by "MPGDTrackerDigi".
    </comment>
    <constant name="InnerMPGDBarrel_2DStrip"                value="1"/>

    <constant name="InnerMPGDBarrelLayer_length"            value="InnerMPGDBarrel_length" />

    <comment> Intrinsic parameters... </comment>
    <comment> ...Thicknesses </comment>
    <constant name="MMCuStratum_thickness"                  value="12*um"/>
    <constant name="MMKaptonStratum_thickness"              value="25*um"/>
    <constant name="MMFR4_thickness"                        value="100*um"/>
    <constant name="MMCuPCBGrd_thickness"                   value="MMCuStratum_thickness"/>
    <constant name="MMKaptonPCB1_thickness"                 value="MMKaptonStratum_thickness * 5"/>
    <constant name="MMCuStrip_thickness"                    value="MMCuStratum_thickness * 3"/>
    <constant name="MMKaptonPCB2_thickness"                 value="MMKaptonStratum_thickness * 4"/>
    <constant name="MMResistive_thickness"                  value="20*um"/>
    <constant name="MMGas_thickness"                        value="128*um"/>
    <constant name="MMMesh_thickness"                       value="18*um"/>
    <constant name="MMGasGap_thickness"                     value="3000*um"/>
    <constant name="MMCuCathode_thickness"                  value="MMCuStratum_thickness"/>
    <constant name="MMCuDriftGrd_thickness"                 value="MMCuStratum_thickness"/>
    <constant name="MMKaptonDrift_thickness"                value="MMKaptonStratum_thickness * 2"/>
    <constant name="MMPCB_thickness" value="MMFR4_thickness + MMCuStratum_thickness * 4 + MMKaptonStratum_thickness * 9 + MMResistive_thickness"/>
    <comment> 2DStrip: Multiple Sensitive Volumes. => Subdivide GasGap: 3 thin slices (pixel and (p|n)strips) at the center, enclosed by 2 thick radiators. </comment>
    <constant name="MMThinGap_thickness"                    value="10*um"/>
    <constant name="MMThickGap_thickness"                   value="(MMGasGap_thickness - MMThinGap_thickness * 3) / 2"/>
    <comment> ...Dimensions </comment>
    <constant name="MMActiveWidth"                          value="340*mm"/>
    <constant name="MMActiveLength"                         value="590*mm"/>
    <constant name="MMFrameWidth"                           value="14*mm"/>
    <constant name="MMOutwardFrameWidth"                    value="80.5*mm"/>
    <comment> r0 corresponds to the outer surface of the PCB. Its value is frozen as of 2026/07, and it serves as an anchor for the other radii, which are more liable to evolve.  </comment>
    <constant name="MMModule_r0"                            value="565*mm"/>
    <constant name="MMModule_rmin"                          value="MMModule_r0 - MMPCB_thickness"/>
    <comment> ...Positioning </comment>
    <comment> The fish scales are implemented as arcs of cylinders, with a center offset and a bisector tilted. Offsets and tilt are thereafter defined in the SECTOR REFERENCE FRAME. External section is shifted w.r.t. internal one along the tilt angle. </comment>
    <constant name="MMInternalSection_x"                    value="11.0857*mm"/>
    <constant name="MMInternalSection_y"                    value="44.4971*mm"/>
    <constant name="MMModule_tilt"                          value="-7.5*degree"/>
    <constant name="MMExternalSection_delta"                value="8.7553*mm"/>
    <comment> Sections are arranged symmetrically about layer's z_offset. Relative positions are here given for sensitive areas, excluding frames. </comment>
    <constant name="MMInternalSection_z"                    value="310.5*mm"/>
    <constant name="MMExternalSection_z"                    value="862.0*mm"/>
    <constant name="MPGDBarrelStave_count"                  value="12"/>
    <constant name="InnerMPGDBarrelLayer_rmin"              value="InnerMPGDBarrel_rmin"/>
    <constant name="InnerMPGDBarrelLayer_rmax"              value="InnerMPGDBarrel_rmax"/>
    <comment> ...Readout </comment>
    <comment> "MMActiveWidth" is to be understood as the width at the top of the PCB (i.e. "r0"). This, as of 2026/07: it may later turn out that it rather corresponds to the neutral axis in the curved PCB. </comment>
    <constant name="r02Sensor" value="MMGas_thickness + MMMesh_thickness + MMGasGap_thickness / 2" />
    <constant name="MMModule_rsensor" value="MMModule_r0 + r02Sensor" />
    <constant name="MMActiveAperture" value="MMActiveWidth/MMModule_r0"/>
    <comment> Strip Cu fraction: There are three Cu strata: 1 = X, 2 = Y, 3 = conductive tracks to connectors. The latter is neglected. DeadZone all along the edges. </comment>
    <constant name="MMnStripsX"        value="192"/>
    <constant name="MMPitchX"          value="1.766*mm"/>
    <constant name="MMSizeStrX"        value="0.7*mm"/>
    <constant name="MMnStripsY"        value="576"/>
    <constant name="MMPitchY"          value="1.021"/>
    <constant name="MMSizeStrY"        value="0.9*mm"/>
    <constant name="MMDeadZone"        value="1*mm"/>
    <constant name="MMCuZoneX"         value="MMActiveWidth  - 2 * MMDeadZone"/>
    <constant name="MMCuZoneY"         value="MMActiveLength - 2 * MMDeadZone"/>
    <constant name="MMCuStrip_fraction" value="(MMnStripsX * MMSizeStrX * MMCuZoneY + MMnStripsY * MMSizeStrY * MMCuZoneX) / (MMActiveWidth * MMActiveLength) * 2 / 3"/>
    <comment> Groundings Cu fractions: groundings are rectangular grids of copper strips. The fraction of copper is taken as size/pitch*2. </comment>
    <constant name="MMSizeStrGrd"    value="0.2*mm"/>
    <constant name="MMPCBPitchGrd"   value="0.8*mm"/>
    <constant name="MMDriftPitchGrd" value="2.4*mm"/>
    <constant name="MMCuPCBGrd_fraction"   value="MMSizeStrGrd / MMPCBPitchGrd * 2"/>
    <constant name="MMCuDriftGrd_fraction" value="MMSizeStrGrd / MMDriftPitchGrd * 2"/>
    <comment> Readout channels: number and pitch. They are both specified independently from the active area. The corresponding constants are needed by the MPGD plugin and the segmentation. </comment>
    <constant name="MMnStripsPhi"    value="MMnStripsX"/>
    <constant name="MMnStripsZ"      value="MMnStripsY"/>
    <constant name="MMPitchPhi"      value="MMPitchX"/>
    <constant name="MMPitchZ"        value="MMPitchY"/>
  </define>

  <materials>
    <material name="MMCuStrip">
      <D type="density" unit="g/cm3" value="8.96 * MMCuStrip_fraction"/>
      <fraction n="MMCuStrip_fraction"        ref="Cu"/>
      <fraction n="1 - MMCuStrip_fraction"    ref="N"/>
    </material>
    <material name="MMCuPCBGrd">
      <D type="density" unit="g/cm3" value="8.96 * MMCuPCBGrd_fraction"/>
      <fraction n="MMCuPCBGrd_fraction"       ref="Cu"/>
      <fraction n="1 - MMCuPCBGrd_fraction"   ref="N"/>
    </material>
    <material name="MMCuDriftGrd">
      <D type="density" unit="g/cm3" value="8.96 * MMCuDriftGrd_fraction"/>
      <fraction n="MMCuDriftGrd_fraction"     ref="Cu"/>
      <fraction n="1 - MMCuDriftGrd_fraction" ref="N"/>
    </material>
  </materials>

  <detectors>
    <detector
      id="TrackerBarrel_2_ID"
      name="InnerMPGDBarrel"
      type="epic_CylinderMPGDBarrel"
      readout="MPGDBarrelHits"
      insideTrackingVolume="true"
      vis="TrackerVis">
      <type_flags type="DetType_TRACKER + DetType_BARREL"/>

      <module name="InnerMPGDBarrelModule" vis="TrackerLayerVis" >
	<comment> Note that "rsensor" must be assigned to the "radius" of the CylindricalGridPhiZ segmentation. The tag is used in the constructor to double-check the consistency between the stack of module_component's and that segmentation radius. </comment>
	<dimensions
            width="MMActiveWidth"
            length="MMActiveLength"
	    r0="MMModule_r0"
	    rmin="MMModule_rmin"
	    rsensor="MMModule_rsensor" />
        <frame name="MMFrame"        material="CarbonFiber" width="MMFrameWidth"        vis="TrackerSupportVis" />
        <frame name="MMOutwardFrame" material="CarbonFiber" width="MMOutwardFrameWidth" vis="TrackerServiceVis" />
        <comment> Components: going outwards, from PCB to drift electrode. The stack-up is taken from Geico_v7. It is simplified as: FR4|Grounding|Kapton|Anode|Kapton|Resistive, where Anode comprises all 4 Cu strata and Kapton includes adhesive and coverlay. The drift stack-up is also, slightly, simplified: Cathode|FR4|Grounding|Kapton. </comment>
        <module_component name="PCBFR4"           thickness="MMFR4_thickness"        material="Fr4"        vis="TrackerModuleVis"/>
        <module_component name="CuGround"         thickness="MMCuPCBGrd_thickness"   material="MMCuPCBGrd" vis="TrackerVis"/>
        <module_component name="PCBKapton1"       thickness="MMKaptonPCB1_thickness" material="Kapton"     vis="TrackerVis"/>
        <module_component name="CuStrips"         thickness="MMCuStrip_thickness"    material="MMCuStrip"  vis="MPGDReadoutVis" />
        <module_component name="PCBKapton2"       thickness="MMKaptonPCB2_thickness" material="Kapton"     vis="TrackerVis"/>
        <module_component name="ResistivePaste"   thickness="MMResistive_thickness"  material="MMGAS_ResistivePaste" vis="TrackerVis"/>
        <module_component name="Gas"              thickness="MMGas_thickness"        material="Ar90IsoButane" vis="MPGDGasVis"/>
        <module_component name="Mesh"             thickness="MMMesh_thickness"       material="MMGAS_InoxForMesh" vis="MPGDInoxVis"/>
        <module_component name="BotRadiator"      thickness="MMThickGap_thickness" material="Ar90IsoButane" sensitive="True" key="3" vis="MPGDGasVis"/>
        <module_component name="phiStripThinGap"  thickness="MMThinGap_thickness"  material="Ar90IsoButane" sensitive="True" key="1" vis="MPGDGasVis"/>
        <module_component name="ReferenceThinGap" thickness="MMThinGap_thickness"  material="Ar90IsoButane" sensitive="True" key="0" vis="MPGDGasVis"/>
        <module_component name="ZStripThinGap"    thickness="MMThinGap_thickness"  material="Ar90IsoButane" sensitive="True" key="2" vis="MPGDGasVis"/>
        <module_component name="TopRadiator"      thickness="MMThickGap_thickness" material="Ar90IsoButane" sensitive="True" key="4" vis="MPGDGasVis"/>
        <module_component name="DriftCathode"     thickness="MMCuCathode_thickness"  material="Copper"     vis="TrackerVis"/>
        <module_component name="DriftFR4"         thickness="MMFR4_thickness"        material="Fr4"        vis="TrackerVis"/>
        <module_component name="DriftCuGround"    thickness="MMCuDriftGrd_thickness" material="MMCuDriftGrd" vis="TrackerModuleVis"/>
        <module_component name="DriftKapton"      thickness="MMKaptonDrift_thickness" material="Kapton"    vis="TrackerMPGDVis"/> <!-- In order to contrast frames -->
      </module>

      <layer module="InnerMPGDBarrelModule" id="0" vis="InvisibleWithDaughters">
        <barrel_envelope
          inner_r="InnerMPGDBarrelLayer_rmin"
          outer_r="InnerMPGDBarrelLayer_rmax"
          z_length="InnerMPGDBarrelLayer_length"
          z0="InnerMPGDBarrel_zoffset"/>
        <layer_material surface="inner" binning="binPhi,binZ" bins0="MPGDBarrelStave_count*24" bins1="100" />
        <layer_material surface="outer" binning="binPhi,binZ" bins0="MPGDBarrelStave_count*24" bins1="100" />
        <rphi_layout
	    x_offset="MMInternalSection_x" y_offset="MMInternalSection_y"
	    phi_tilt="MMModule_tilt" phi0="0.0"
	    delta="MMExternalSection_delta"
	    nphi="MPGDBarrelStave_count"/>
        <z_layout
	    z0="0.0" z1="MMInternalSection_z" z2="MMExternalSection_z"/>
      </layer>
    </detector>
  </detectors>

  <plugins>
    <plugin name="DD4hep_ParametersPlugin">
      <argument value="InnerMPGDBarrel"/>
      <argument value="layer_pattern: str=InnerMPGDBarrel_layer\d"/>
    </plugin>
  </plugins>

  <readouts>
    <readout name="MPGDBarrelHits">
      <comment>
        Each of the 5 Sensitive Volumes has a distinct segmentation tag, the
        X-reference being done in the detector builder.
        The grid_size's of the Helper Volumes (reference and radiators) are
        arbitrary, to some extent.
        Here, they are set equal to the detector's resolution. They may,
        eventually, be set equal to its pitch.
      </comment>
      <segmentation name="2DStrip" type="MultiSegmentation" key="strip">
        <segmentation name="Reference"   type="CylindricalGridPhiZ" key_value="0" grid_size_phi="1*mrad"           grid_size_z="0.150*mm*sqrt(12)" radius="MMModule_rsensor" />
        <segmentation name="PhiStrips"   type="CylindricalGridPhiZ" key_value="1" grid_size_phi="MMPitchPhi"       grid_size_z="MMActiveLength"    radius="MMModule_rsensor - MMThinGap_thickness" offset_phi="MMPitchPhi/2" />
        <segmentation name="ZStrips"     type="CylindricalGridPhiZ" key_value="2" grid_size_phi="MMActiveAperture" grid_size_z="MMPitchZ"          radius="MMModule_rsensor + MMThinGap_thickness" offset_z="MMPitchZ/2" />
        <segmentation name="BotRadiator" type="CylindricalGridPhiZ" key_value="3" grid_size_phi="1*mrad"           grid_size_z="0.150*mm*sqrt(12)" radius="MMModule_rsensor - 3 * MMThinGap_thickness / 2 - MMThickGap_thickness / 2" />
        <segmentation name="TopRadiator" type="CylindricalGridPhiZ" key_value="4" grid_size_phi="1*mrad"           grid_size_z="0.150*mm*sqrt(12)" radius="MMModule_rsensor + 3 * MMThinGap_thickness / 2 + MMThickGap_thickness / 2" />
      </segmentation>
      <id>system:8,layer:4,module:12,sensor:2,strip:28:4,phi:-16,z:-16</id>
    </readout>
  </readouts>

</lccdd>
